 <H1>Where do ICs Come From?</H1> 
 <P><UL>
<LI><H2>ICs are based upon the semantics of the real-world enterprise that is being described in the database relations. 
</H2>
</UL><UL>
<LI><H2>We can check a database instance to see if an IC is violated, but we can NEVER infer that an IC is true by looking at an instance.
</H2>
<UL>
<LI>An IC is a statement about all possible instances!
<LI>From example, we know name is not a key, but the assertion that sid is a key is given to us.
</UL></UL><UL>
<LI><H2>Key and foreign key ICs are the most common; more general ICs supported too.</H2>
</UL></P>
